\subsection{4. A novel term premium with $r^\ast_t$ and $\pi^\ast_t$}

\begin{frame}
  \frametitle{4. A novel term premium with $r^\ast_t$ and $\pi^\ast_t$}
  \begin{wideitemize}
  \item When modeling the yield curve, forecasting interest rates, or
    estimating bond risk premia, we need to account for the trend
    component $i^\ast_t = r^\ast_t + \pi^\ast_t$
  \item This insight is important for estimating the term premium:
    \[ y_t^{(n)} = \frac{1}{n} \sum_{j=0}^{n-1} E_t i_{t+j} +
      TP_t^{(n)} \]
  \item Compare TP estimates from two different approaches:

    \begin{wideitemize}
    \item Stationary VAR for PCs of yields $Y_t = (y_t^{(1)}, \ldots, y_t^{(N)})'$
    \item Stationary VAR for PCs of \alert{detrended} yields
      $\tilde{Y}_t = Y_t - \iota_N i^\ast_t$
    \end{wideitemize}
  \end{wideitemize}
\end{frame}

\begin{frame}
  \frametitle{Term premium based on VAR in levels}
  \begin{figure}
